FBIS3-56421 "drsov011_b_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Fedorov Announces Conditions for Remaining in Government LD1701205794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1956 GMT 17 Jan 94 LD1701205794 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Boris Fedorov has put the following conditions to his joining the government as the minister of finance: Aleksandr Zaveryukha should not be the deputy prime minister and the president should not confirm Viktor Geraschenko as the head of the Central Bank. In a brief interview to the journalists on Monday evening [17 January] in the lobbies of the State Duma B. Fedorov said that he had written a letter asking to join the membership of the Banking Subcommittee of the Plans and Budget Committee of the State Duma. According to B. Fedorov he also made a decision to join the Union of December 12 group of deputies headed by the deputy premier of the Moscow government Aleksandr Braginsky.
